ygData.subject: Re: Looking for a weblink
ygData.msgSnippet: Stick to using www.WTFcomics.com as they frequently change servers, the IP address changes but the domain follows them wherever they roam. Also,
ygData.messageBody:
Stick to using www.WTFcomics.com as they frequently change servers,
the IP address changes but the domain follows them wherever they roam.
Also, www.mobhunter.com has comics as well as interesting and humorous
articles.

--- In EverQuest@yahoogroups.com, "Wulfric Rennison" <wulftech@e...>
wrote:
> I feel kinda stupid asking this.
>
> One day while sitting in class ignoring my professor's lecture, I
was browsing the web and came across a weblink. It was a series of
comic strips based on EverQuest that I thought was really well done.
I had intended on posting the link to this list, but never did. Now
I'm trying to find the link again but I cant remember how or where I
found it. So I was hoping that maybe someone here might know what I'm
talking about. Essentially the comic strip starts out with a female
wood elf turning in her quest paper to become a druid, but some things
happen and she ends up being taken under the wing (?) of an Iksar who
was a friend of her father. The Iksar character is named after the
person's character who draws the strip. Hopefully this is enough
information that someone might recognize it and post the link.
>
> Thanks in advance.
>
> Wulfric
